"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Barcomi&#39;s ended up being my favorite dining experience in Berlin. We rode bikes through the side streets to hunt out this hidden brick courtyard deli, where you can wheel your bicycles right through and park them next to your  table.<br><br>A NY style deli, I couldn&#39;t not go for a fresh bagel with homemade cream cheese (you can get Philadelphia, but why would you??).  And I added a lovely coffee from south America (they have info on their extensive coffee offerings on their website, score!).<br><br>Husband got a quiche and a lemon tart. All cakes and treats are vegetarian friendly, without any animal fats or gelatin. (If you&#39;re lactose intolerant, gluten intolerant or vegan just ask, they are very on the up and up about that stuff).<br><br>It was a little on the pricey side, but considering their quality of ingredients and in-house policy on making just about everything, I think it&#39;s worth it. Service was really friendly and it was just a really relaxing, atmospheric stop in our day",
