"ogimage":"http://s3-media1.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/WNbNKka_HpriVZKROiBuMQ/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"Giant burgers for a decent price.<br>My husband and I came here a few weeks ago on a weekend night and it was packed!  We ended up sitting outside despite the cold (I&#39;m pretty sure the staff thought we were crazy) because they had nice outdoor seating and it was quieter.  I didn&#39;t get a good look or feel for the interior atmosphere but it is definitely a popular spot and it seemed like there were big groups of friends hanging out, which is cool.<br><br>They have a lot of burger options.  It took me forever to decide but I ended up going with the peanut butter burger and my husband got one of the spicy burgers (I can&#39;t remember what it was called).  The bartender/server guy was nice enough, not rude but clearly not trying to charm you.<br><br>The burgers are very wide and on the thinner side, which is how I like mine, and loaded with toppings.  And then there are the potatoes wedges!  They were soooo good and the homemade onion dip was to die for.  Aside from the tasty burgers, the potatoes and dip would definitely bring me back in.<br><br>The burgers are around 10 euro each which seems to be about average for the &#34;nicer&#34; burger joints in Berlin (i.e. White Trash, The Bird, etc).  We couldn&#39;t even finish our whole burgers so I think we got our moneys worth.<br>People on Yelp seem to be complaining mostly about the non-burger food and the service.  I don&#39;t know why you would expect good nachos in Germany at a non-Mexican/Tex-Max restaurant...  If you want a big tasty burger and you are fine with servers with an edge, Room 77 is a good option for you.",
