"ogimage":"http://s3-media4.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/gIIFk9dVVtB6Xoyt2Yvxpw/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"As I was able to convince my companion to try a restaurant I haven&#39;t been to before, we went here, which was a short ride from where we were. I&#39;ve heard only good things about this place, and sure enough, this place delivered.<br><br>As this was a Vietnamese place, I couldn&#39;t pass the opportunity to test them by ordering a bowl of pho ga, and I paired it with real authentic Vietnamese coffee. My companion on the other hand ordered a rice bowl mixed with water spinach, and she also ordered a lemongrass tea. <br><br>The place was still not busy, although we already saw several tables that were reserved for the night. Our food came out quickly, and we were amazed at the pretty presentation. It looked tasty, and sure enough, it tasted good as well. <br><br>The place is a little expensive; my small Vietnamese coffee was 3,40 EUR, but it was so worth it. I loved that little cup of sweet goodness, I was almost tempted to order another one, but I feared I wouldn&#39;t be able to sleep later.<br><br>Overall, we paid 24,80 EUR plus tip. A little pricey for Berlin, and a little pricey for the quantity, but this place is more quality than quantity. I&#39;ll be back here again. I suggest asking for a place in the terrace when the weather is good. There are plenty of good nooks and crannies to bring a date and be intimate during a meal.",
