"ogimage":"http://s3-media4.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/mPXwi76kv2X8XcUIdPze7g/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"I would say this was my first &#34;real&#34; german meal.... Was recommended to this place by a Berlin local and I have to say I am  a fan - the generous portions and heavy carbs may be a turn off to some, but to me, it was comfort food deliciousness!! <br>For our mains, my sister and I did the old half/half switch trick - which meant I got to try two different dishes, we chose Käsespätzle a cheesey, chewy pasta that with every mouthful I was thinking about the next, as well as the Rheinischer Sauerbraten which was a braised meat with red apple cabbage and potato dumplings. <br>The servings were HUGE! and although I was feeling full, decided to share a dessert. The three of us shared the Süßer Flammkuchen (Sweet Flambee) which was kind of like a dessert pizza/tart with apple and raisons with a shot poured over an set on fire - the flames added a bit of drama to the meal - it was quite exciting. <br>My only negative of the meal was the shot of alcohol poured over the dessert... I get that this is how the fire is lit, but it was a little overpowering in some parts which were quite heavily soaked in alcohol. Apart from that, I would recommend this place to anyone wanting an authentic german meal in berlin!!",
