"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/bwqoEqb_ydZC2zt5iJkDPA/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"It&#39;s no Ruth Chris or Morton&#39;s but by golly it&#39;s pretty decent &#34;American&#34; fare. I&#39;d say it&#39;s like a Black Angus or Ruby Tuesday, an upscale coffee shop which features steaks, served with a house salad, baked potato with their &#34;house&#34; sour cream and a hunk of garlic bread.<br><br>The American dressing for the salad was more like 1000 island, while the French was more like Ranch dressing. Go figure.<br><br>I had the rib eye and my server thought I said Well instead of Rare. No biggie, it got sent back and came back perfectly cooked, piping hot!! The steak was tender but a tad salty from their seasoning. I devoured it anyway.<br><br>Stephen had the special prime and it looked as tender as it tasted. He finished his meal as well.<br><br>Quite honestly I can&#39;t find fault with our meal. My steak was €20,50 which is no different than what I pay in SoCal. I did sub the sour cream for the herb butter, and was glad I did. The German sour cream is thick, and not as creamy as the US version.<br><br>I would recommend this place and would come back too.",
