"reviewcomment":"A friend of mine and I visited this place in the Mitte.<br><br>I instantly fell in love. There is an outside patio area to sit on and enjoy your meal. There is also seating inside. There are pictures around the cafe. There are also French products to purchase.<br><br>This is a self service place, so I would advise to pick out which table you will be seated at and then go order. They will ask where your table to located.<br><br>I went here about 4-5 times for breakfast after discovering it, and I always ordered the same thing. <br><br>--Cappuccino which was strong and excellent. Way better than our watered down coffee in America..<br>--Rhubarb Tart, this was so delicious. It was sweet enough, and I loved the tartness which in my opinion balanced out the sweetness.<br><br>There was some language barriers, but some of the baristas spoke English and we made it work. <br><br>I am really going to miss this place!",
