"rating":"3.0",
"reviewcomment":"After finally trying out a Currywurst at Konnopke&#39;s Imbiss (not as spectacular as I&#39;d expected, but it was ok), I was walking homewards and happened to walk past An einem Sonntag im August.  It caught my eye, so I walked in.<br><br>I really, really liked the atmosphere here.  There were glass doors separating the spacious main area from the smoking room, and they seemed to actually work! (unlike some other places I&#39;ve been to...but then again, there weren&#39;t any smokers at the time).  Lining the long wall were three large wooden &#34;steps&#34; padded with cushions and regularly interrupted by small tables with menus, pots of sugar, and books.  These stair/benches were decently but not super comfortable, but I still I enjoyed sitting there--it was the perfect people-watching spot, with great views out the large windows of the street.<br><br>Also in the café were sofas (which I later moved to), plentiful outlets, WIFI, and delicious drinks.  On the slightly pricier end of things, but the warm red currant juice (with a hint of cinnamon!) that I ordered was absolutely delectable.<br><br>Coming back for sure!",
