"reviewcomment":"In my opinion, this is without a doubt one of the best places I have found in Berlin for Coffee. The cappuccino is technically perfect: a strong shot of dark brown, freshly roasted espresso topped with thick, creamy (full fat) milk with a dusting of chocolate and served with an amaretti biscuit.<br><br> On offer is a wide range of cakes, chocolates and other calorie laden sweet things which are pretty much irresistible to the hardiest dieter. Also worth noting is the nice selection of salads and sandwiches on offer during lunching hours, which in Berlin is anything from 1100 - 1800.<br>However, some may find the smell alone in the adjacent store to be satisfactory enough - you can buy all of the Coffee that they serve in the café and more, freshly ground. On offer is a wide range of high quality chocolate from Berlin, Germany and further afield such as Switzerland &amp; Austria.<br><br> Bear in mind, you do pay for the privilege of having an exceptional coffee in a fairly nice neighborhood, as a cappuccino was around 3,80EUR but it&#39;s so worth it!",
