"reviewcomment":"Ok, look, I have no idea what Indonesian, Singaporean or Indian food and I&#39;m no specialist which may explain why I think that&#39;s a cool place. That being said, the service was rather friendly and I was not even &#34;hooked&#34; by them while walking, I just thought that I could try the place because it had some decent food and I felt hungry (happens from time to time).<br><br>Here you may order a lunch menu (till 17h) for 5,50€ which seems very low to be but Berlin is definitely not a pricey place. I went for a vegetarian meal made from lentils mostly. I was also given an appetizer &#34;biscuit&#34; (spicy) along with a tomato sauce and the some flat-bread. Everything tasted really good already. I took a mango-yoghurt drink to go with that, for smoothing all the upcoming spiciness. Fair trade and organic, always good to know, but 2,90 which is quite high in comparison with the meal itself. Also took an Indian tea at the end, not amazing but OK with an honey aftertaste.",
