"ogimage":"http://s3-media4.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/0HZPYUeaDiUway5eW_bwHA/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"This is a cool place, with chunky modern dark wood tables and benches inducing a convivial atmosphere, as one often has to share the larger tables with strangers. The glass walls are illuminated by funky color-changing lights and adds to a slightly surreal ambience, like a fancy place from the film Blade Runner.<br><br> The food is generally very tasty, Thai of origin, with a healthy blend of Vietnamese and Singaporean, and you can order small or regular portions. My usual trick is to get a few starters and then order the 1 kilo of fried fresh king prawns, which means that one must always come here with a friend as that&#39;s a lot of prawns!<br><br> Service is usually pretty good, unless the place is packed, which is quite often during the weekends, so reservations are definitely recommended.<br><br> Overall, it&#39;s a nice place to take friends who want to try an unusual modern Asian bistro, and that&#39;s what I do.",
