"reviewcomment":"we arrived in berlin extremely hungry. by now, we&#39;d been on a 7-8 hour flight from delhi, followed by a 2-3 hour wait until we boarded multiple trains that took hours to get us from frankfurt to berlin. <br><br>the place with the best reviews was dicke wirtin - right around the corner from our hotel, and later we discovered was also suggested by our hotel. <br><br>the sign was very misleading being placed where it was. there was a door right next to it and we walked in only to find an empty abandoned building within. we were very confused, then peeped around the corner and found the patio and restaurant we were looking for.<br><br>the menu gives a brief background about the place:<br>&#34;welcome... in our typical berliner restaurant in a comfortable atmosphere directly in the berlin city-west.<br>located on savignyplatz in charlottenburg, the dicke wirtin (fat landlady) has been a berlin institution for decades and a student stronghold since the heady days of the 1960s demonstrations.<br>the clientele is a mix of students and locals who come here to dig into hearty portions of traditional german homemade dishes.<br>9 different beers on tap &amp; more than 30 in house brandies and liquers.&#34;<br><br>we each ordered a beer - i had the schnedier weisse hef and my s.o. had a pilsner. we ordered a riesen-bockwurst (large frankfurter) and the charlottenburger : zwiebelrostbraten vom rumpsteak mit bratkartoffeln &amp; salat or, onion beef roast with fried potatoes and salad (top left). between this &#34;burger&#34; as they called it (really it was just a steak/burger patty with an au jus type dressing, topped with grilled onions) and our beers, we were pretty full - but then we saw the warmer apfelstrudel (warm apple strudel with custard and cream).  a lot of people raved about this dessert, and i&#39;m a sucker for a warm apple dish, so we got it, and we&#39;re so glad we did. <br><br>we wanted to come back to dicke wirtin for at least a beer and another apple strudel, but unfortunately, our stay in berlin was very brief... and it was on to the next!",
