"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"I&#39;ve had so much amazing Italian food while in Berlin... I didn&#39;t think it was possible to eat this good! Gorgonzola Club definitely tops the list.<br><br>Terrace seating out front, romantic dark interior with a lot of space, and a lovely little garden terrace nestled in the back of the restaurant. The menu was extensive - pasta, pizzas, main dishes, appetizers, etc. <br><br>We started the meal with a glass of Prosecco and a plate of bruschetta. The bruschetta is a bit different than the stale toasts topped with tomatoes that many are used to, instead it comes out looking a bit like a pizza and tasting a lot like heaven. A thin dough topped with juicy tomatoes, olive oil and tons of garlic. Don&#39;t skip it! <br><br>Next, I had the seafood pasta which was one of the daily specials. I received a large portion of spaghetti in red sauce filled with the tiniest, sweetest clams, shrimp, squid, and so on. The dish was delicious. <br><br>I also tried a bite of pizza that a friend ordered - it was very tasty. <br><br>We finished the meal with an espresso. The food was on-point and memorable. The service was also impeccable.<br><br>Whether you&#39;re in the area or not, Gorgonzola Club is worth a visit!",
