"ogimage":"http://s3-media2.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/uKYYF8j3GC8oIspZzoRwxw/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"I met a companion here for breakfast one weekend. He happens to be vegan, and from out of town, and was staying in Pankow. So my task was to find a place that is vegan-friendly, near the Pankow area, and open for breakfast at 9:00 AM, as we only had a two-hour window to meet, due to other imposing constraints. I found this one.<br><br>I found the shop very welcoming, and very clean. I arrived when they were still not open, and the staff was already hard at work arranging the fresh flowers they put on the tables, and so forth. When we entered, we found a table by the end of the room, and they gave us menus. English menus are also available, which my companion appreciated very much.<br><br>I ordered the spinach omelette, which came with a side salad, as well as a pair of English muffins that had some pesto spread on it. They were all vegetarian, and very tasty. I also ordered a Milchkaffee, which was very well-made.<br><br>I am not a vegetarian anymore, but at least I know there are good options like these in the city. I&#39;d go back here again if I am with someone who doesn&#39;t eat meat and needs a little bit of variety.",
