"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"I was super excited to come for multiple reasons. Firstly, I was stoked to finally have made it to a Yelp event, secondly I love exploring new restaurants, and thirdly I love Scandinavian food.<br><br>Munch&#39;s Hus is in an area I normally don&#39;t frequent that much, but it is super close to a U-Bahn stop, so getting here is really easy. The atmosphere of the restaurant is very cosy with Norwegian music playing in the background. The menu ranging is not big, but all the dishes sound delicious and the ones we had, all were able to keep up with our expectations. It took me some time to be able to decide, but with a beer in one hand and Elkblood (mixed drink from berries and vodka - oh god), I was finally able to make my decision. I went with the Kjottkaker, Norwegian meatballs (I am sure many of you know the Swedish/Ikea version of that Köttbullar). I received 3 massive hand-made meatballs, potatoes and cabbage. Everything was delicious and filled me up to the max. <br><br>The service at Munch&#39;s Hus was also great. Very attentive waiters, who were up to explaining everything, if we had any questions. The prices are also ok, considering the quality and service.<br><br>All in all, a great discovery and I will definitely be coming back at some point.",
