"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/TqCmK90v3YwUfKwSdgTPlA/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"I was here the other day, having lunch with a friend I haven&#39;t seen since 1995. We were surprised that we both ended up living in Berlin, so we decided to meet up one day and have lunch together. We both work near Mitte, so after agreeing to meet near Checkpoint Charlie, we strolled around and found this Japanese restaurant. <br><br>As it was lunch, they had lunch set menus, so we both opted for the Menu A, which included 8 nigiri sushi, 6 pieces of maki sushi, a couple of other pieces, and miso soup. I paired mine with green tea, as usual. My meal cost about 15 EUR, which, as far as I can tell, is on the higher side, but I think with this one, I am willing to pay for that. Here&#39;s why.<br><br>First, I loved the soup. Miso soup sounds so easy to make, but if you mess up the ingredients, then it&#39;ll fail. They know what they&#39;re doing. The subtle taste of the soup was great. Second, the fish was on the fresh side. No, it&#39;s not glistening fresh, but it will do. I also liked the way they flavored the eel, with just the right amount of sweetness. <br><br>Overall, this is a good sushi place, at least, better than the others I have encountered. I am fine giving them 4 stars, which means that I am comfortable bringing people to lunch here. Probably not for dinner, but it will do for a lunch meeting or something similar.",
