"reviewcomment":"After wandering all about Viktoria Park this afternoon, a nosh and a drink were in order. I started to hit up the historic bungalow place, but wasn&#39;t feeling it - as I wandered up Kreuzberger Strasse I noticed STAROPRAMEN DARK on the awning...<br><br>Say WHAT? Czech Cerny pivo on TAP? No way.<br><br>Yes way.<br><br>So, after confirming the menu looked good and that Staropramen Cerny was -actually- available... I settled in and ordered a schnitzel. With the schnitzel came a salad that was - well, really terrible. I&#39;ll just pretend that wasn&#39;t actually delivered to my table.<br><br>Also included was a pile of fries, and those were fine - but here&#39;s the deal: All that was 3,75 euros. Adding the beer and a single scoop if ice cream brought my total to 6,75. For a full meal. Again, pretending that sad little salad never appeared. (honestly - epic piles of mayo does not make for a good &#39;dressing&#39;)<br><br>The waitress was friendly, prompt and quite helpful. I enjoyed tipping her.<br><br>The two guys sitting next to me ordered the Angus Burger - which looked AWESOME. Kinda grumpy I didn&#39;t get one of those myself... ok, not really. Next time for sure. Also: A table tent advertises a plate of wild North Sea mussels for 8,90. Thats gonna be a return trip item for sure.",
