"ogimage":"http://s3-media1.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/H2Tlh-fTszQ51ji0W3NVSw/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.0",
"reviewcomment":"I just got back a week ago from a trip to Europe, and my favorite beer on the trip was from Brauhaus Georgbraeu!  We later went to Augustiner Keller and Hofbrauhaus in Munich, but I still prefer the Georgbraeu beer.  <br><br>When we first arrived, it took us a few minutes to find a waiter and get seated.  It wasn&#39;t too packed when we arrived and in fact, the atmosphere was not at all what I expected.  We were seated at a booth inside and it had a cozy/homey feeling to it.  We ordered a traditional German dish-- the pork knuckle that came with stewed peas, sauerkraut, and potatoes.  All for 9.99 Euros and it included one 0.2 liter glass of beer.  It was plenty to feed the both of us!  We also ordered another 0.2 liter glass of beer so we tried both the pale and the dark beer.  How I wish I could have more now!  I really enjoyed the beer, but I was too full at the time to drink more.  I&#39;ll definitely go back if I&#39;m ever back in Berlin and see if it&#39;s as great as I remember.  =)",
