"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"My companion brought me here last night for dinner. We made a reservation early in the day, which was actually useful because when we got there at 20:00, it was rather crowded. Hence, we were able to sit down in a large cubicle without waiting at all.<br><br>I selected items from the Winter Limited menu. I got a potato and goose stew, followed by a Rapunzel Salad (salad greens with apples, tomatoes, and fried goose liver). That was good. My companion on the other hand got a big pot of mussels in tomato and garlic sauce. <br><br>This place is relatively cheap, compared with other establishments that serve the same quality food. Main courses hover between 8 to 12 EUR, and the food is more pub food rather than swanky white linen. They also have some specialty beers on tap. <br><br>The missing star is due to the service. It&#39;s a little slow and unenthusiastic, as with many places here in Europe. If you need something, you have to grab the person&#39;s attention, as they won&#39;t do a good job monitoring every table making sure that the diners are satisfied with their dining needs. So if you need more napkins, or you want your plate of mussel shells emptied because it is not big enough, then you have to explicitly ask for that.",
