"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"OK, I confess, Herr Lehmann is one of my favorite films.  And that is probably why I made sure to come to Markthalle on my first trip to Berlin.  However, this is my fourth trip to Berlin, and I&#39;ve been to Markthalle each time, and sometimes multiple times.<br><br>I&#39;ve always come for dinner- just love this beer hall&#39;s roomy and ever so slightly nicer than average atmosphere, and I&#39;ve found the food to be consistently my favorite German food in its price range.   The Schweinebraten is indeed excellent, and I&#39;ve enjoyed the Schnitzel several times too.  I&#39;m not much of a steak eater, but I had an awesome one here on my last trip- so I ordered it again on my next visit and it was merely very good,- so I may have just had the perfect cut and perfect preparation the first time,- but I do say if you are a couple traveling and one of you wants to try a German specialty in a Beer Hall, and the other wants to stick to a steak, I think this is the place for you!<br><br>The wine list has actually proved pretty good- not extensive, but what we&#39;ve had we&#39;ve liked.  Service has always been very good, and it&#39;s been quite busy when I&#39;ve been in.  My only wish is that  Karl from Herr Lehmann would come out and wait my table with their finest bottle of wine in hand...",
