"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/fgp3GtsufJ_QJXj4qJGYCA/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"All right, I&#39;m fibbing a bit on the Price Range bar below, giving this a rating of cheap which means 7 Euro or less.  The menu is three courses for 7.5 Euros.  At least that was the last time I was at Cafe Nord-Sud in September.  I will be there again within 3 days as I am Berlin-bound today, and can&#39;t wait to have lunch at Nord-Sud again soon.<br><br>If you are looking for fine dining, this isn&#39;t the atmosphere- it is absolutely casual, and as far as I can tell a two man show.  The owner/server is usually frantically busy, but remains to my mind extremely charming.  I always feel like I am seeing a theatre piece when I am here, as once the place is full, and it often is, he is definitely pulling off a performance piece to keep things running.<br><br>There are three menus each day.  Each is a different 3 course meal.  No mixing and matching, no interchanging,- you pick one and get those three courses.  One of the three has always had a main course of fish, and one has always been red meat or pork when I&#39;ve dined here.<br><br>Coming from the San Francisco Bay Area, I am always thrilled to be here and get a three course French meal for an amazing price.  And I very much appreciate the energy and dedication it takes to make it happen.<br><br>For travelers on a budget, who like French Cuisine, and especially those who appreciate the eclectic, Cafe Nord-Sud is worth a special trip.",
