"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"I was here for lunch today. I didn&#39;t bring lunch to work, so I took a lunch break, took the U-Bahn, and headed here for lunch. I didn&#39;t have a human companion, so I took my book with me. As I already bookmarked this months ago, I was curious to see how this restaurant does given my standards.<br><br>They have a very small fixed menu, plus a daily menu that is ever-changing. You can find what they are cooking on their website, as well as written on the blackboard displayed in the restaurant. <br><br>I ordered the potato stew (large portion), as well as a latte macchiato. Service was quick (well, they&#39;d only scoop up a portion into a serving bowl), and the taste was good. I typically like restaurants with small menus; that&#39;s typically a sign that they do it well. I&#39;d rather pick a restaurant with a small menu, than one that has tons of possibilities, because I am not sure you can really deliver good food if you&#39;re trying to make lots of variants. <br><br>I also liked the atmosphere inside. It&#39;s not grandma-chic, but it definitely has an original feel to it. The tables are old, you almost expect it to smell musty, but that&#39;s just an illusion. I love the atmosphere, especially in the back room. I&#39;d totally come back here, either with a date, or with friends, drinking.",
