"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"From the minimalistic decor - the light dusty blue walls, the modern meets vintage lightbulbs hanging from the ceiling - to the open sushi bar, to the &#34;i want everything on there&#34; menu, Omoni is my favourite Korean (bordering on Japanese) kitchen in Berlin.<br><br>Ooooor, at least it shares the no. 1 spot with Yam Yam, but whereas I go to Yam Yam for a bibimbap craving, korean pancakes and dumplings, I go to Omono for the more sushi like options. <br><br>I have a tendency to order the same things: the tuna tartar rolls ($4.80) are beyond tasty, and serve as the perfect entree. For a main it&#39;s all about #15 ($8.50):  a rice bowl served up with both raw and cooked salmon, salmon skin and bio-salad - hearty, yet fresh at the same time. And oh yes, the seaweed salad is pretty amazing too. <br><br>The place is popular, and is only open for dinner, so make sure to book if you are more than two people. Otherwise try to get a seat at the bar and watch the chef do his magic!",
