"ogimage":"http://s3-media2.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/p66JjQn6H78OnB5QlK7QFw/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Walking up street, I immediately spotted the storefront to this Japanese restaurant- it&#39;s hard to miss with the most colorful and cute artwork painted on the storefront windows. <br><br>This is truly a special and unique place that will transport you to Japan. You will completely forget you&#39;re in Berlin as you enter this hip and very pink restaurant. Yumi (lady who runs the place) and the staff are all super-friendly - It was so nice to see so many happy smiling faces. With a little smile of my own, I ordered and settled in for a yummy meal and a feel-good Japanese cultural experience. <br><br>The menu is simple, fresh and authentic Japanese home cooking - the kind of stuff you&#39;d find coming from a real Japanese kitchen including: Grilled fishes, Yakiniku beef, Miso tofu, Teriyaki Chicken, Noodle bowls, Sushi, Japanese rice porridge and a range of authentic side dishes. The dishes are carefully prepared and arrive the table looking picture perfect - how often do you get a salad with little carrots cut into cute little flower shapes? <br><br>They also have bento boxes which are packaged boxes filled with a variety of tasty bites portioned and sectioned to make a really healthy and convenient meal to go. Growing up in Hawaii, I remember being able to grab these types of bento boxes all over the place. Seeing the bento boxes on the counter brought back some nice memories and I&#39;ll definitely be back to grab one next time I need a quick meal to go.<br><br>I also found out that Smart Deli also has an online food order/delivery service. The order form is on their website. I took a look and there is a nice wide range of all the Japanese basics you&#39;d need to cook a nice meal at home. So, if you&#39;re feeling inspired to cook some Japanese food in your own kitchen, you&#39;re all set here!<br><br>Before I left, Yumi came over to chat with me as I was looking at a flyer for an upcoming event they were hosting with handmade crafts and food demos. It was such a nice treat getting to learn about her life and the restaurant. Felt like being at a friends house for lunch and sitting around chatting after. All her hard work definitely shows as I found out it happened to be their 10 year anniversary on the day I was there and I got a free homemade smiley face cookie for their birthday as part of the celebration. <br><br>What more can I say? Go check this place out - you&#39;ll be hooked too",
