"reviewcomment":"Awesome service. Packed - make reservations. Pakistani food, NOT indian, as the only other english language reviewer, with no &#39;Friends&#39;, and one review, stipulates. It&#39;s not personal, or anything to do with her, though. It&#39;s this retarded, buggy &#39;Yelp&#39; system - eliminating many helpful reviews and yet leaving in a review from 2011, from a one-off reviewer.<br><br>{Edit: please also hunt for the mis-categorized  review from &#39;slowfood&#39;. &#39;It&#39;s too sweet/westernized&#39;, goes the review; worth reading. However, given the local community, this is expected. Menu items 108 through 113, are the hot and spicy items. And if you especially want hot and spicy, be sure to ask.}<br><br>Service was good, prompt; much more than can be expected for the city-area generally. This ethnic &#39;proud of my restaurant&#39; shines through. People spoiled on non-local service standards, may easily miss the extra, here, that good service provides.<br><br>The chai was respectable. The salzig lassi could have been saltier; otherwise excellent (salt to taste).<br><br>The fried vegetables were done correctly with a chickpea dough instead of wheat.<br><br>Murgh Salat was very sweet - not offensive - but sweeter than what i want for an evening meal. The mango pulp content made it incredibly sweet - i don&#39;t think any sugar was added. Says something for pakistani mangos, though. Mixed Pakora was good, however, again, the sauce was sweeter than i would have liked. A meat dish will be next.  ...<br><br>Music was not too loud. Bathrooms were private, heated and clean.<br><br>If you had a good experience at this restaurant, please let us know. If you want to thank me for this review, please mark below. Thanks :)",
