"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"My companion and I had a quick bite here before we headed to the symphony. We wanted a döner, but we didn&#39;t want to wait 45 minutes to get one. And since another companion of mine suggested this as an alternative, we headed here to try it out. The fact that it was very close to the metro station was also a good plus.<br><br>We didn&#39;t realize that there were two lines, which separates chicken and beef. It wasn&#39;t clear at the outset, so while we were still eyeing our options, the guy at the empty counter said &#34;Bitte schön&#34; and so we ordered. When we learned it was the chicken stand, I was a little disappointed, but still ordered one, as the beef stand had about 5 people lined up.<br><br>Anyway, even though it was chicken, it was a great choice, great enough that I am willing to give it 4 stars. I only wonder what the beef tasted like. But since the waiting time isn&#39;t 45 minutes, I am more than willing to give it a try. This is definitely a great alternative to the more famous one, though I still say that there is a reason why there is a 45-minute wait on the other one, because it really is very good.",
