"rating":"3.0",
"reviewcomment":"I was here with a companion yesterday for lunch. I was interested in what they offer since most of the South Asian restaurants I find here in Berlin are so tame and non-spicy at all, as they taper the taste to the German palates. So I didn&#39;t have high expectations of this place.<br><br>Anyway, when we got there, the place was not crowded at all, but we can see several tables marked reserved, and I suppose that was a good sign. I ordered a vegetarian aubergine curry, as well as a mango lassi. My companion on the other hand ordered some samosas and a lentil curry. <br><br>They gave us some of those crisp wafers for appetizers. The sauce was hot and spicy. That was a good sign. I almost wanted to order a portion of raita to cool things down, but my mango lassi did the trick as well. I liked the eggplant as well as the spiced coconut that came with it. My companion didn&#39;t like the samosas too much, however. <br><br>Overall, I am giving this place 4 stars, because for the first time, I found a place that serves spicy food. However, their service needs improvement. But then again this is Europe, customer service isn&#39;t on par with that in North America. So expect a little bit of a delay when you finally decided what you want to order and want to tell it to the waiter.",
