"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"One of the best meals I&#39;ve had in Berlin. Absolutely perfect in every way. I came with a party of 6, we were seated immediately and met with very friendly service right away. We ordered some calamari, the appetizer sampler and some carpaccio. Everything was nothing short of incredible. The wine was delicious, they didn&#39;t make any fuss about bringing 6 hungry guys bread every 20 seconds as we inhaled it.<br><br>For the main I ordered the farfalle with salsiccia. it was so good! Al dente house-made pasta (very fresh anyway, if not house-made), seasoned and sauced perfectly, and just the right amount. I&#39;m a big eater and this left me in great shape, not too stuffed, not wanting more.<br><br>I tried my friend&#39;s calzone which was so nice and perfectly spicy. Very well made. <br><br>The ambience is nice, the music selection is incredible (this was one of the main points of the guy in our group who took us here), and the service was fast and friendly. Prices are definitely decent. It&#39;s not the cheapest night out, but for 3 apps, 6 mains, 3 bottles of great wine and a bottle of sparkling water we ended up at €35 each. Pretty damn good, I think!<br><br>Highly recommend this place. Good for dates and small groups, though not a place to be loud and wildly festive.",
