"reviewcomment":"Three stars aren&#39;t much but if you haven&#39;t been at Ovest I do warmly recommend coming here, at least once, then it is up to you if you decide to come back for seconds.<br><br>It is not as much about the culinary experience as it is about an anthropological journey. Of course you need to be into such kind of things and not everyone is. But if you are keep reading.<br><br>This is your classic Berlin Italian Nouveau-riche restaurant with a twist. All bets are off, guest moderation left at the door -of their houses- and they all come to this establishment to truly show some skin. <br>From kids drinking Moet to Oligarchs with their daughter age companions and grandmas equipped with miniskirts dancing on tables, it is a fest of all goes and let me be myself in this world that is only beauty and utopia, at least for me. <br><br>So if escapism to the surreal is what you need come and join me at Ovest. I&#39;ll be the guy in the Gorilla suit smoking  a cigar inside their smoking chamber.",
