"reviewcomment":"By chance, I found myself on a beautiful Saturday at Kaffee Raum. Thank you, chance! Thank you. <br><br>Kaffee Raum is a beauty. Clean, sparkly, plenty of outside tables, counter service, lovely light menu and desserts...it&#39;s calling your name! <br><br>I had just finished a massage at Schoenerie (across the street) and wasn&#39;t quite ready to head back home and tend to my chores. IN fact I was walking around like a noodle, dazed. Need some coffee! I spied Kaffee Raum and popped in quietly, took a seat at a plush green couch in the corner, settled up with a good book....<br><br>A bowl of Cafe Au Lait (a bowl! I love it...) and the eggs, bacon and toast plate was just perfect. A light little brunch that left me full, but not feeling heavy. A quiet place to read (it seems a lot of readers cluster inside!) and polite service.<br><br>I returned again for a breakfast meeting a few days later, and enjoyed their outside seating, sunshine, the Fitness Fruhstuck (I liked the one at Alpenstuck Backeri a bit better) which was nice...and another bowl o&#39; coffee. Cheers all around... <br><br>Definitely a lovely cafe. A part of the coffee rounds (Grounds?) from now on. :)",
