"ogimage":"http://s3-media2.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/NCUJrMwLPrO7anZoMPhezw/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"We ate here one night on a recent stay in Berlin, as it was close to our apartment. The place was quite quiet, with less than half the tables full, so we could choose any table we wanted. We sat outside, with those lovely fleecy throws that everyone in Berlin seems to use (a GREAT idea, by the way - can we make this catch on in other places too please?).<br>The restaurant had a pleasant atmosphere, with some quiet music and everyone talking amongst themselves. The waitress who greeted us was helpful and attentive and spoke excellent English. Overall, it looked very nice and we decided it was as good a place as any, so we gave it a shot.<br>And then the food arrived! Oh my, but it was tasty!! All six of us went quiet for quite a long time as we devoured everything on our plates. It was all so fresh and tasty, and just...just lovely. Above all else, it was the meat that did it: cooked to absolute perfection - so much so that it makes my mouth water thinking about it even now...",
