"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"A friend and I were hungry after work and decided to go out for dinner last week. As we were both after ethnic cuisine, we decided to try Shayan, a Persian restaurant in Schöneberg. After dinner, we emerged full and satisfied.<br><br>We decided to try the Appetizer platter for two. It included a bunch of things, like eggplant dip, pickled rice in grape leaves, some fried fritters, spinach and raisin balls, and so forth. That was cool, I liked it. <br><br>For the main dish, I tried the fessenjan, as I figured I should try this signature dish in every Persian restaurant I visit. It was amazing; the pomegranate sauce was so rich and perfect for the fragrant rice that it came with. Not to mention that the chicken pieces that were simmering in it were bigger than how I have seen it so far. <br><br>My friend on the other hand tried a lamb curry with peanuts and raisins. She let me try it, and I have no complaints on that either.<br><br>So overall, the place was a good experience. The restaurant was small, but cozy. Enough room for two yuppies feeling lazy and wanting dinner after work.",
