"reviewcomment":"Whatever you take here it will be tasty. On the plate or in bread you will have your falafel served with fresh tomatos and a dainty cabbage salad. 2,50 Euro for a sandwich, 4 or 4,50 for a plate. My fav is the halumi plate (with fried cheese). The pity is that they do not serve the parsley salad with it. And if you still wish you will have to pay 50 cent more which is not such a big deal after all.<br><br> I prefer this place in summer as you can also sit outside and if not, the door is still open so you can breath. In winter it is quite cold inside as they save by not heating, and then your clothes will smell like an old falafel for the rest of the day. Lately they stoped serving free tea so now you have to pay to get one.<br><br> P.S.<br>A couple of months ago I used to like this place but I am changing my mind. It seems they are getting worse every day Last week I took a Halumi Plate and discovered that the portion got noticeable smaller. May be the crisis is to blame for that but I do not think I gonna visit them again soon.",
