"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"After seeing some good reviews for Phuket on TripAdvisor (and because its name incited immature giggles), we decided to give it a go.  <br><br>Walking in, the ambience was perfect--beautiful Thai decorations made us feel like we were transported to an exotic food paradise.  The service was quite friendly but a tad slow (this may have been because we were sitting in a corner, enjoying the view from the window).<br><br>We ordered two items: Menü 3 (duck in red curry) and Menü 9 (prawns in sweet and sour sauce), which both came with a side of soup (we got one vegetable, and one hot and sour soup).  Because we got there on a weekday, between 12 and 5pm, each dish was 5,90 euros.  <br><br>All the food was fantastic--both for the eyes and the stomach.  We were particular fans of the duck in red curry and hot and sour soup, but we wouldn&#39;t recommend it to anyone who can&#39;t tolerate spicy food.  (I&#39;d say the curry was mild to medium spicy.)<br><br>SUMMARY<br>* fantastic atmosphere (semi-classy--good for inviting parents, guests but still casual)<br>* great food<br><br>Coming back again!",
