"rating":"3.0",
"reviewcomment":"Well. So, I&#39;m wandering about Alex trying to guess if the construction will ever be over... and decide I want a drink and a nature break. I spy slices in the window and think &#34;mmm pizza&#34;. Once I entered, I realized its a white tablecloth place, but sat and checked out the menu (in English as well as Italian and German)... glad I did!<br><br>Lunch specials are a great deal. 6,30 euros for Medallions Pomodoro. I could see into the kitchen (not the best view usually, but this was fine in this case) and saw the cook cutting the medallions off the pork loin and pounding them out for my dish. Can&#39;t beat that for fresh! A salad arrived (twas a bit more &#39;oil&#39; and a bit less &#39;vinegar&#39; for my taste). Service was attentive and swift. Nice place to sit and watch the world of Alex go by. Note: They did nick me 3 euros for a diet coke. C&#39;est la vie. Gotta make the coin somehow.<br><br>I&#39;d have liked a basket of bread to go with the meal - guess I&#39;m used to that showing up in the US and you have to order it here... but the meal was excellent. The potatoes were just a tad salty, and the broccoli was pretty forgettable - but the sauce was **magnificent**. 3.5 stars. Oh heck. They get 4 since I can&#39;t do half stars... they get the extra half star for not being a tourist trap.<br><br>Note: Like most places the bathrooms are downstairs. Not ADA accessible my any means. But then, neither is most of Europe.",
