"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"I came here to do a beer brewing course conducted by Thorsten Schoppe, a man who looks more at home in a dojo than a brewery. However, looks can be deceiving as this gentleman really knows his stuff. The course was quite interesting and it was even more interesting to hear the (long detailed) questions asked by the other attendees (Germans take their beers very seriously). So I actually learnt quite a lot.<br><br> Lunch was also provided and it was pretty ordinary - what one would expect from any kneipe in Berlin. The place is quite big, with a stage for live music, so it looks like a happening sort of place in the evenings and weekends.<br><br> Well, I have now concocted my own beer recipe (thanks to Thorsten&#39;s expert guidance) and all I now need is an empty basement to make my brew...<br><br> By the way, we were compelled to sample the beers here and the general verdict was that it&#39;s &#34;nicht schlecht&#34;, which, as it came from German beer pros, translates roughly in English to &#34;damn bloody good - gissus another!&#34;.",
